Since F^0 is sent to \operatorname {Gr}_0^W(T_\mathbb {C}(M)), it is thus of type (0,0).

fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let X be a compact Khler variety (for example, smooth and projective). By the holomorphic Poincar lemma, the de Rham complex \Omega _X^\bullet is a resolution of the constant sheaf \mathbb {C}. We thus have an isomorphism () \operatorname {H}^\bullet (X,\mathbb {C}) \sim \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^\bullet (X,\Omega _X^\bullet ) and the stupid filtration on \Omega _X^\bullet () defines the hypercohomology spectral sequence
